what are the purpose we using network interface in AWS ?

    ENIs are virtual network cards you can attach to your EC2 instances. They are used to enable network connectivity for your instances, and 
    Having more than one of them connected to your instance allows it to communicate on two different subnets.

ENI presents with public and private IP.
ENI has associated with Security group

We create ENI in one AZ, we can associate with same AZ. Network Interface will not supported to attach for Another AZ & Region.

Within same AZ for ENI & EC2, we can attach multiple ENI in single instance.

To Monitor network flow:
3. We can configure Flow logs in ENI (Ethernet Network Interface)
2. We can configure Flow logs in Subnet
1. We can configure Flow logs in VPC level
TCP port number = 6
UDP port number = 17